column1: #Text=The Portland Trail Blazers ( 7 - 10 ) defeated the Los Angeles Lakers ( 2 - 13 ) 108 - 96 on Friday at the Moda Center in Portland .
#Text=The Trail Blazers got off to a quick start in this one , out - scoring the Lakers 34 - 21 right away in the first quarter .

#Text=The Trail Blazers were the superior shooters in this game , going 49 percent from the field and 40 percent from the three - point line , while the Lakers went 44 percent from the floor and just 30 percent from deep .
#Text=The Trail Blazers were led by the duo of CJ McCollum and Damian Lillard .
#Text=Lillard went 9 - for - 19 from the field and 5 - for - 11 from the three - point line to score a game - high of 29 points , while also adding seven assists .
#Text=He 000s combined for 37 points over his last two games , as he continues to be a force on the boards .

column1: #Text=Lillard on the other hand shot 12 - for - 20 from the field and 4 - for - 7 from the three - point line to score 28 points .
#Text=It was his second strong showing in a row , as he 000s combined for 56 points and 22 rebounds over his last two games .
#Text=The only other player to reach double figures in points was Kobe Bryant , who came off the bench for 21 points ( 7 - 20 FG , 1 - 5 3Pt , 6 - 7 FT ) , two rebounds and two assists .
